      "message": "[info] Line 115: sanitizePreferredPort is a good safety measure. Suggest making the non-privileged range explicit using named constants and assert the upper bound (65535) for clarity and future maintenance. Also add a short note that this sanitization is applied because peer-supplied hints are untrusted.\n\nSuggested change:\n```suggestion\nstatic constexpr quint16 PREFERRED_PORT_MIN \u003d 1024;\nstatic constexpr quint16 PREFERRED_PORT_MAX \u003d 65535;\n\nquint16\nsanitizePreferredPort(const QVariant\u0026 value)\n{\n    const auto port \u003d servicePort(value);\n    // Only accept non-privileged ports in [PREFERRED_PORT_MIN .. PREFERRED_PORT_MAX].\n    return (port \u003e\u003d PREFERRED_PORT_MIN \u0026\u0026 port \u003c\u003d PREFERRED_PORT_MAX) ? port : 0;\n}\n```\nRationale: makes intent explicit and protects against invalid values above 65535 if servicePort implementation changes.",
